=== 2026-02-21 14:00 — Gradle 9 breaking changes research ===
- User asked for Gradle 9 migration guide, specifically for Kotlin+Vaadin build.gradle.kts
- Researched: Vaadin 25 plugin + Gradle 9, Kotlin 2.3 + Gradle 9, all breaking changes
- Key findings:
  1. Vaadin 25 Gradle plugin IS compatible with Gradle 9 (officially supported)
  2. Kotlin 2.3.x plugin IS compatible with Gradle 9.0-9.3
  3. jcenter() fully removed in Gradle 9 (project already uses mavenCentral, no issue)
  4. kotlinOptions{} deprecated since Kotlin 2.0, should use compilerOptions{}
  5. tasks.withType<KotlinCompile> should use .configureEach (lazy) not eager config
  6. mainClassName removed in Gradle 8; project already uses mainClass.set() (OK)
  7. Java 25/Corretto 25: Gradle 9.1 works from CLI but IDE may show false errors;
     Kotlin 2.3.0 added JVM_25 target support
  8. Gradle 9 embeds Kotlin 2.2 for .kts scripts; JSpecify replaces JSR-305 nullability
  9. Configuration Cache now preferred mode; reproducible archives default
  10. Minimum KGP version is 2.0.0; project uses 2.3.10 (OK)
- Current build.gradle.kts already mostly correct; only needs .configureEach on withType
- No files changed
