=== 2026-02-21 14:30 — Research: vaadin-boot webapp/ROOT structure ===
- Researched vaadin-boot 13.6 by mvysny — what Env.findWebRoot() expects
- Source: common/src/main/java/com/github/mvysny/vaadinboot/common/Env.java (main branch)
- findWebRoot() calls Env.class.getResource("/webapp/ROOT") on classpath
  - If ROOT file missing → IllegalStateException crash
  - Strips "/ROOT" suffix to get webapp/ directory URL
  - Purely classloader-based, NOT filesystem-based
- Minimum requirement: src/main/resources/webapp/ROOT (marker file, any content OK)
- ROOT file content in examples: "Required by Vaadin Boot" or similar comment text
- Example structures from 3 repos:
  - vaadin-boot/testapp-kotlin: webapp/ROOT only
  - vok-helloworld-app: webapp/ROOT + webapp/images/ (static assets)
  - vaadin-boot-example-gradle: webapp/ROOT + webapp/icons/icon.png + webapp/styles.css
- Project currently missing webapp/ directory entirely — needs to be created
- No files changed
