=== 2026-02-21 14:03 — Research: UPC barcode → media metadata APIs ===
- Researched current options for looking up DVD/Blu-ray/HD media metadata from UPC barcodes
- Categories investigated:
  1. UPC→product databases (UPCitemdb, Barcode Lookup, Go-UPC, EAN-search.org, Open Products Facts)
  2. Movie/TV metadata APIs (TMDB, OMDb) — neither supports UPC directly
  3. Physical media specific (Blu-ray.com scraping, DVDUPC.com)
  4. Amazon PA-API (supports UPC→ASIN, but being deprecated April 2026)
  5. Wikidata (P3962 property for GTIN/EAN/UPC, but sparse coverage)
  6. MusicBrainz (audio discs only, not video)
- Recommended approach: two-step — UPCitemdb (free, 100/day) for UPC→title,
  then TMDB (free, ~50 req/sec) for title→rich metadata
- Kotlin/Java libraries found: tmdb-kotlin (app.moviebase:tmdb-api:1.5.0),
  tmdb-java (UweTrottmann), openmoviedb-api (Kotlin/Ktor OMDb wrapper)
- No API provides disc-level detail (what's on each disc in multi-disc sets)
- Full summary delivered to user
