=== 2026-02-28 12:10 — Fix Dialog rendering inline on split Transcode views ===
- Problem: After splitting TranscodeView into sub-pages (Status, Unmatched,
  Linked, Backlog), Dialog components rendered inline at page bottom instead
  of as floating overlays on /transcodes/unmatched and /transcodes/linked.
- Root cause: Vaadin 25's pre-compiled bundle lazy-loads Dialog in a separate
  JS chunk (chunk-b6f90b2b). The chunk is transitively loaded via hash
  039da0aa... on pages like CatalogView (which uses IntegerField/Checkbox),
  but the Transcode sub-pages only use base-bundle components (Grid, Button,
  TextField, ComboBox) that don't trigger any chunk loading.
- Failed attempts: @Uses(Dialog::class) annotation, hidden Checkbox in initial
  render — neither triggers the Dialog chunk in the pre-compiled bundle.
- Fix: Added onAttach() override to both TranscodeUnmatchedView and
  TranscodeLinkedView that calls executeJs with
  window.Vaadin.Flow.loadOnDemand('039da0aa...') to force-load the Dialog
  chunk on page attach.
- Removed ineffective @Uses(Dialog::class) annotations and hidden Checkbox
  workaround from both views.
- Verified: Dialog and Notification custom elements register correctly;
  Link dialog on Unmatched page opens as proper overlay; re-transcode
  confirmation on Linked page expected to work similarly.
- Files modified: TranscodeUnmatchedView.kt, TranscodeLinkedView.kt
