=== 2026-03-02 23:30 — Docker deploy + OOM diagnosis ===
- Added --disable_local_transcoding CLI flag to Main.kt (gates TranscoderAgent.start())
- Updated Dockerfile: COPY transcode-buddy/ for build, added --disable_local_transcoding to CMD
- Updated docker-compose.yml to match deployed version (mem_limit: 4g, memswap_limit: 4g)
- Built and pushed Docker image 202603022323 to NAS registry
- OOM diagnosis: cAdvisor showed "memory cached" spiking within 1-2 minutes of startup
  - Root cause: TranscoderAgent.cleanupBadCodecFiles() on startup walks entire ForBrowser/
    directory and runs `ffmpeg -i` on every MP4 to probe codecs
  - Each probe causes kernel to page-cache chunks of multi-GB MP4 files
  - Hundreds of files × several MB cached per probe blows past 4 GB cgroup limit
  - With --disable_local_transcoding, TranscoderAgent never starts, no probes run
- Deployed new image, confirmed "Local transcoding DISABLED" in logs
- Monitoring memory stability
