=== 2026-03-06 19:38 — Fix video playback on Roku, Safari, and Chrome iOS ===

Problem: Video playback worked on Chrome desktop but was broken on Roku,
Safari/iOS, and Chrome/iOS.

Root cause 1 — Truncated moov atom (Roku + Safari):
- VideoStreamServlet had maxChunkSize = 2 MiB for Range responses
- Voyager S03E01 ForBrowser MP4 has a 3 MB moov atom (ftyp→moov→mdat)
- Video trak (1.3 MB) fit within the 2 MB cap, but audio trak (starts at
  1.3 MB, extends to 3 MB) was truncated
- Roku: entered "playing" then immediately errored with -5 "malformed data"
  and availableAudioTracks=[] (audio trak metadata cut off)
- Safari: similar failure parsing incomplete moov atom
- Fix: increased maxChunkSize from 2 MiB to 16 MiB

Root cause 2 — Unsolicited 206 (Safari fix, Chrome iOS still broken):
- Applied FEATURES.md 9g: all requests (with or without Range header) now
  return 206 Partial Content capped at 16 MiB
- This avoids streaming entire 700 MB+ files in one response
- Safari iOS started working; Roku already working; Chrome iOS still broken

Root cause 3 — Missing playsinline attribute (Chrome iOS):
- <video> element lacked the `playsinline` attribute
- On iOS, without playsinline, video attempts fullscreen takeover
- Safari handles this gracefully; Chrome's WKWebView does not
- Chrome iOS downloaded 160 MB of video data (10 × 16 MB chunks) but
  refused to render it
- Fix: added `playsinline` to the <video> element in VideoPlayerDialog

Investigation approach:
- Connected to Roku debug console (ncat port 8085) and captured error logs
- Probed ForBrowser MP4 with ffprobe: verified H.264 High, AAC-LC, faststart,
  no SEI NALs — encoding was correct per spec
- Compared bytes through Synology HTTPS reverse proxy vs direct — identical
- Used /admin/requests endpoint to compare Safari vs Chrome iOS behavior:
  Safari made sustained range requests; Chrome burst-downloaded then stopped

Files modified:
- VideoStreamServlet.kt: maxChunkSize 2→16 MiB, unified 206 path for all
  requests (no-Range treated as bytes=0-), removed separate 200 full-file path
- VideoPlayerDialog.kt: added playsinline to <video> element
- FEATURES.md: marked 9g done, updated 9 status (playback working)

