=== 2026-03-09 20:30 — Fix session revocation notification delay (#6) ===
- Fixed notifications not appearing immediately after session revocation
- Root cause: with PushMode.AUTOMATIC, dialog.close() + Notification.show()
  in the same handler caused the notification to be swallowed by the dialog
  close. Fixed by wrapping Notification.show() in ui.access {} to ensure it
  flushes as a separate push, and moving refreshGrid() before dialog.close()
- Fixed in ActiveSessionsView.kt: revokeItem() and confirmRevokeAll()
- Fixed in UserManagementView.kt: deleteUser(), resetPassword(), ratingCeiling()
- Also closed #15 (multi-season wish duplicates) — already fixed by season-aware
  wish list implementation in Phase 2

=== 2026-03-09 21:27 — Periodic TMDB popularity refresh (#4) ===
- Created PopularityRefreshAgent background daemon
  - Cycles every 4 hours with 10-minute startup delay
  - Dynamically computes batch size: ceil(total/600) per cycle ≈ 1%/day
  - Full catalog refresh completes in ~100 days
  - Refreshes both Title.popularity and CastMember.popularity
  - Cast members grouped by tmdb_person_id (one API call per person)
  - Respects TMDB rate limits (500ms between API calls)
  - Stops batch on API errors, handles InterruptedException for clean shutdown
  - Uses Clock interface for testability
- Added V050 migration: popularity_refreshed_at column on title and cast_member
- Updated Title and CastMember entities with new field
- Wired agent into Main.kt with shutdown hook
- Files created: PopularityRefreshAgent.kt, V050__popularity_refresh_tracking.sql
